definitions.text: I am possessed, am under the power of an evil-spirit or demon.
an evil-spirit, demon; a heathen deity.
I bite; hence: I backbite, harm seriously.
Dalmanutha, a town or village near Magdala.

Dalmatia, a province of the Roman Empire, east of the Adriatic, a later
                  name for part of what was earlier called Illyricum.
I tame, subdue, involving obedience and restraint.
a Damascene, an inhabitant of Damascus.
I spend, bear expense, waste, squander.
but, on the other hand, and

a weak adversative particle, generally placed second in its clause;
                  but, on the other hand, and.

it is necessary, inevitable; less frequently: it is a duty, what is
                  proper.
an example, type; a thing shown.
I hold up as an example
I hold up as an example, make a show of, expose.

I point out, show, exhibit; met: I teach, demonstrate, make
                  known.
I shrink, am fearful, timid, cowardly.
so and so, such a one

so and so, such a one, where the name of the person is known but not
                  used.
a dinner, an afternoon or evening meal
a dinner, an afternoon or evening meal.
respectful of what is divine, religious

respectful of what is divine; religious, perhaps, rather than
                  superstitious (the usual meaning).
religion in general; in a bad sense: superstition.

Decapolis, meaning a group or district of ten cities (of the Greek
                  type) in Palestine, mostly south-east of the Lake of Tiberias; the names and
                  number vary in ancient authorities.
I allure, entice by a bait
one posted on the right hand, a spear-man
one posted on the right hand, a spear-man.
on the right hand, right hand, right
on the right hand, right hand, right.
I want for myself; I want, need; I beg, request, beseech, pray.

Derbe, a town in Lycaonia and in the southern part of the Roman
                  province Galatia.
the skin or hide of an animal.
I bind, put in chains, tie together.

a bond, chain, imprisonment; a string or ligament, an impediment,
                  infirmity.
a keeper of a prison, a jailer
a keeper of a prison, a jailer.

(originally: hither, hence) (a) exclamatory: come, (b) temporal: now,
                  the present.
come hither, come, hither, an exclamatory word.
on the second day, on the next day

adj. where English requires an adv., on the second day, on the next
                  day.
second-first, a word of uncertain meaning.
second, in the second place, for the second time

second; with the article: in the second place, for the second
                  time.

I bind, tie, fasten; I impel, compel; I declare to be prohibited and
                  unlawful.

(a) in a clause expressing demand: so, then, (b) indeed, (c)
                  truly.
Demas, a helper of Paul in Rome.
I make a public speech, address a multitude
I make a public speech, address a multitude.
an artisan, builder, maker; one who labors for the public.

properly: the people, especially citizens of a Greek city in popular
                  assembly, but in NT, multitude, rabble.
a denarius, a small Roman silver coin.

of course, indeed, qualifying and yet strengthening the
                  assertion.

(a) gen: through, throughout, by the instrumentality of, (b) acc:
                  through, on account of, by reason of, for the sake of, because of.
I cross, pass through, step across.
I thrust through, slander, complain of, accuse.

(adj. used often as a noun), slanderous; with the article: the
                  Slanderer (par excellence), the Devil.
I announce throughout, spread the news of

I announce throughout (the world), spread the news of, give notice of,
                  teach.
I pass (of time); I continue through, intervene.
judicial examination, decision; an act of discernment.
I awake out of sleep, am thoroughly awake
I awake out of sleep, am thoroughly awake.
I spend time, pass time, live
(either trans. or intrans.), I spend time, pass time, live.
I receive in my turn, receive through another.
I offer here and there, distribute, divide
I offer here and there, distribute, divide, hand over.
I gird, tie around; mid: I gird round myself.

(a) a covenant between two parties, (b) (the ordinary, everyday sense
                  [found a countless number of times in papyri]) a will, testament.
I divide into parts, cut asunder, distribute.

I wait at table (particularly of a slave who waits on guests); I serve
                  (generally).
waiting at table; in a wider sense: service, ministration.

a waiter, servant; then of any one who performs any service, an
                  administrator.
I hear throughout, of a judicial hearing
I hear throughout, of a judicial hearing.

I separate, distinguish, discern one thing from another; I doubt,
                  hesitate, waver.

distinguishing; hence: deciding, passing sentence on; the act of
                  judgment, discernment.

I converse together, talk of; of conversation passing from mouth to
                  mouth.
I converse, address, preach, lecture; I argue, reason.
I cease, give over, give up
I cease, give over, give up.
language, speech, conversation, manner of speaking.
I become reconciled to, reconcile myself with
I change, exchange; I reconcile, change enmity for friendship.

a calculation, reasoning, thought, movement of thought, deliberation,
                  plotting.
I give solemn evidence, testify solemnly
I give solemn evidence, testify (declare) solemnly.
I divide up into parts, break up, distribute
I divide up into parts, break up; I distribute.
I divide into portions, distribute; pass: I am spread about.
I am in trouble, doubt, difficulty
I am in trouble, doubt, difficulty; I am at a loss.

(lit: I saw through), I cut to the quick (with indignation and
                  envy).

lit: scattering abroad of seed by the sower, hence: dispersion, used
                  especially of the Jews who had migrated and were scattered over the ancient
                  world.
I give a commission (instructions), order; I admonish, prohibit.

I save (rescue) through (some danger), bring safely to, escaped
                  to.
I give orders to, prescribe, arrange.
(a) I appoint, make (of a covenant), (b) I make (a will).
I tarry, continue, stay in a place.
I shine through, dawn (of the light coming through the shadows).
I carry through, differ, surpass, excel

(a) trans: I carry through, hither and thither, (b) intrans: I am
                  different, differ, and sometimes: I surpass, excel.
I destroy, waste; hence met: I corrupt.
I lay my hands upon, slay, kill
I lay my hands upon, and so: I slay, kill.
I separate myself from, part from
I separate myself from, part from, go away.
able to teach, apt to teach
able to teach, apt to teach.
a double-drachma, two drachmae, a Greek silver coin.
the Twin; Didymus, the Greek name equivalent to Thomas.
I offer, give; I put, place.
I wake out of sleep, I arouse
I wake out of sleep, arouse in general, stir up.
a public spot in a city
a meeting-place of roads, a public spot in a city.
I pass through, spread a report
I pass through, spread (as a report).
two years old, lasting two years.

a period of two years, two years; according to ancient practice this
                  means any period between one and two years.
I relate in full, describe, narrate.
between two seas, which has sea on both sides.
I pass through (to), come through (to), pierce.
I put apart, separate, put some distance between
I put apart, separate, put some distance between.

just; especially, just in the eyes of God; righteous; the elect (a
                  Jewish idea).

(usually if not always in a Jewish atmosphere), justice, justness,
                  righteousness, righteousness of which God is the source or author, but
                  practically: a divine righteousness.
I make righteous, defend the cause of, justify

I make righteous, defend the cause of, plead for the righteousness
                  (innocence) of, acquit, justify; hence: I regard as righteous.
a thing pronounced to be just

a thing pronounced (by God) to be righteous (just, the right); or the
                  restoration of a criminal, a fresh chance given him; a righteous deed, an instance
                  of perfect righteousness.
acquittal, justifying, justification, a process of absolution.

(a) (originally: custom, usage) right, justice, (b) process of law,
                  judicial hearing, (c) execution of sentence, punishment, penalty, (d) justice,
                  vengeance.

the Dioscuri, Castor and Pollux, sons of Zeus and Leda, and patrons of
                  sailors.

(lit: twain-mouthed; hence: of a sword, as a drinker of blood),
                  two-edged.
I strain, put through a sieve
I strain, put through a sieve.
I set at variance, make to be hostile
I cut asunder; met: I set at variance, make to be hostile.
I cut in two, scourge severely
I cut in two, perhaps: scourge severely.
(lit: of two souls, of two selves), double-minded, wavering.

I subject to regulations, decree; mid: I subject myself to regulations,
                  am decree-ridden.
I think, seem, appear, it seems
I think, seem, appear, it seems.
I put to the test, prove, examine

I put to the test, prove, examine; I distinguish by testing, approve
                  after testing; I am fit.
a trial, proof; tried, approved character
a trial, proof; tried, approved character.
a test, trial, what is genuine
a test, trial, what is genuine.
a beam or spar of timber.
I act deceitfully, deceive, use fraud.

honor, renown; glory, an especially divine quality, the unspoken
                  manifestation of God, splendor.
I glorify, honor, bestow glory on
I glorify, honor, bestow glory on.
Dorcas, the Greek name of Tabitha.
I bring into subjection, enslave, treat as a slave.
I am a slave, am subject to, obey
I am a slave, am subject to, obey, am devoted.
a dragon or huge serpent; met: Satan.
I take hold of, grasp, catch.
a drachma, a Greek silver coin.
Drusilla (born A.D. 39), daughter of Herod Agrippa I.
(a) I am powerful, have (the) power, (b) I am able, I can.

(a) physical power, force, might, ability, efficacy, energy, meaning
                  (b) plur: powerful deeds, deeds showing (physical) power, marvelous works.
I empower, fill with power, strengthen.

(lit: a man who rules by force), a ruler, potentate; also: courtier,
                  member of the court.
I am powerful, have power, am able, am mighty.
(a) of persons: powerful, able, (b) of things: possible.
difficult to interpret, hard to be understood.
difficult, hard; of persons: hard to please.
a setting of the sun, the West
a setting (of the sun), hence: the West.
evil report, defamation, words of ill omen.

twelve; the usual way in which the Twelve apostles of Jesus are
                  referred to.
the roof (of a house), the top of the house.
as a free gift, without payment, freely
as a free gift, without payment, freely.
